🟧 Installation and configuration
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	

Originally I installed postcss autoprefixer. But I uninstalled it, Tailwind v4 don't require.

1) Tailwind CSS Engine + tools

	> npm uninstall @tailwindcss/postcss postcss autoprefixer
	> npm uninstall @tailwindcss/vite
	> npm uninstall tailwindcss
	
	> npm i tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite -D
	
2) configure vite.config.js
	1. import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite'
	2. plugins; [] --> tailwindcss()
	3. add, CSS: { extract: true} --> to handle CSS extraction, example dynamic class handling
         
3) Take a look index.html

	<script type="module" src="./index.js"></script>
	
	- style.css is imported in index.js
	
	- This is the magic part: The Vite development server intercepts this request.
	- It looks in your source folder and finds index.ts
	- It then serves the generated JavaScript back to the browser.

4) I have installed prettier code formatter and its Tailwind CSS plugin 
	> npm install -D prettier prettier-plugin-tailwindcss
	
	> Add commands in package.json "scripts: -
		"format:check": "prettier --check .",
    		"format": "prettier --write ."	
    		
	> npm run format --> to clean up code. It will sort Tailwind classes and save.
	
   
