		public show() {}
		--> modalContainer.classList.add("active");
		
	and in
		public close() {}
		--> modalContainer.classList.remove("active");

/*** important: Jason to check ***/		
4) Animation: i.e. opacity transition for dutation of 300s, wouldn't work without setTimeout()
	Suggested:
		// 1. Start the fade-out transition
  		modalContainer.classList.add("opacity-0");
  		// 2. After the animation finishes, hide it from the layout
		  setTimeout(() => {
		    modalContainer.classList.add("hidden");
		  }, 300); // Must match the transition duration
		
5) pointer-events:none and pointer-events:auto are redundant in modal.ts
	public show() and public close()
	
	ex: modalContainer.classList.remove("hidden", "opacity-0", "pointer-events-none");
	
	Because, when modal is "hidden" already makes the element non interactive.
	and when modal is visible, by default div is pointer-events: auto 


