🟧 Configure VS code settings.json to ignore some Linter errors
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)  In html id="modal-container", I have 'hidden' and 'flex' classes setting the same property.
    Lint correctly flags this. But this is intentional conflict, resolved with Javascript. 
    Linter lacks this context.

	So I have added in settings.json of vscode, this line -
	"tailwindcss.lint.cssConflict": "ignore"

	But it didn't remove the warning.

2) In style.css, @apply shows error Unknown at rule @applycss(unknownAtRules)

	Linter is wrong because it doesn't know about Tailwind's special syntax.

	However, the rule "css.lint.unknownAtRules": "ignore" is very specific and 
	the risk is extremely low.

	The most important thing to understand is that VS Code's linter is just 
	a helpful guide; it is not the real error checker.

	The real authority on whether your Tailwind CSS is correct is the Tailwind compiler, 
	which is run by Vite every time you save a file.

	I added in VS settings: Preferences: Open User Settings (JSON)     
	
	"css.lint.unknownAtRules": "ignore"




